^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|This was actually an easy hand to bid and play. Kia has a clear opening bid, and Ally, especially because she is short in the majors, has a nice 3C bid. I would have opened my hand 2C. Basically, if Kia has the @HK or @CA I want to be in six. Normally it is not a good idea to bid Blackwood with a void. But I was willing to assume one of Kia's key cards was the @DA, and I just needed one additional key card from him. On some hands you have to "picture" partner's hand. This is one of them.|
