NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I only have 16 HCP, but opposite only 3 HCP (the heart King) I can make slam. The points don't matter on this hand. All that matters is if Kia has the cards I need, which are the club Ace and the heart King. That is one thing good players learn to do on distributional hands, where point count is very inaccurate. They picture what partner needs, and if the bidding says it is likely, they bid what they think they can make.|
